commit_list.message:
OK. I believe I did everything you asked, and more.

* Added descriptive comments, and doc tests. Removed non-functional comments.
* Renamed some of the intrinsics, all of the "pub fn" declarations have been renamed.
  As long as it is well documented which intructions they correspond to, I think
  it might actualy increase the user base by making them easier to recognize.
* Removed some of the #[inline] declarations where it made stuff slow.
* Added read_u32v_be back from before, and removed .to_be() inside the blocker.
* Removed the `_safe` versions since they seem to be about the same speed on ARM.
* Remove all `transmute()` uses. It turns out I was transmuting from an array to a slice,
  and then transmuting that slice back to an array. It made no sense. Sorry about that.
* Cleaned up the structs, namely, refactoring `h1`, `h2`, `h3`, to an `h` array.
* Cleaned up some of the non-intrinsics with tuple selectors (v.0, v.1, ...).
